# Validation Patterns

Use express-validator for input validation middleware.

## Structure

```typescript
import { body, query } from "express-validator";

// Shared validation rules
const emailValidation = body("email")
  .isEmail()
  .withMessage("Must be valid email");

// Validation chains for endpoints
export const createValidation = [
  body("field1").exists().withMessage("field1 is required"),
  body("field2").isString().withMessage("field2 must be string"),
  body("field3").optional().isDate().withMessage("field3 must be date"),
];

export const updateValidation = [
  body("field1").optional().withMessage("field1 is optional"),
  body("field2").optional().isString().withMessage("field2 must be string"),
];
```

## Common Validators

```typescript
// Required field
body("name").exists().withMessage("name is required")

// Optional field
body("bio").optional().isString()

// Date validation
body("birthDate")
  .exists().withMessage("birthDate is required")
  .isDate().withMessage("birthDate must be valid date")

// Enum validation
body("gender")
  .isIn(["MAN", "WOMAN"])
  .withMessage("gender must be MAN or WOMAN")

// URL validation
body("profilePictureUrl")
  .optional()
  .isURL()
  .withMessage("must be valid URL")

// Query param validation
query("id")
  .exists()
  .isUUID()
  .withMessage("id must be valid UUID")
```

## Create vs Update

```typescript
// ✅ Create: fields are required
export const createPersonValidation = [
  body("name").exists(),
  body("gender").exists(),
  body("birthDate").exists().isDate(),
  body("deathDate").optional().isDate(),
];

// ✅ Update: all fields optional
export const updatePersonValidation = [
  body("name").optional(),
  body("gender").optional(),
  body("birthDate").optional().isDate(),
  body("deathDate").optional().isDate(),
];
```

## Reusable Rules

Extract common validations:

```typescript
// ✅ Define once, reuse in multiple chains
const genderEnumValidation = body("gender")
  .isIn(["MAN", "WOMAN"])
  .withMessage("gender must be MAN or WOMAN");

export const createValidation = [
  body("name").exists(),
  body("gender").exists(),
  genderEnumValidation,  // Reuse
];

export const updateValidation = [
  body("name").optional(),
  genderEnumValidation,  // Reuse
];
```
